title: UMass women's soccer gets back over .500 with 4-2 win against Rhode Island (photos)
text:
Comments 
The University of Massachusetts women's soccer team got back over .500 for the season with a 4-2 home win over Rhode Island at Rudd Field Sunday. 
Backed by goals from Julia Weithofer, Erin Doster, Laura Johns and Jackie Bruno, the Minutewomen came back from an early 1-0 deficit to improve to 6-5-3. Cassidy Babin made one save in net for UMass. 
The Minutewomen are next in action at Duquesne Thursday. 
Check out the above photo gallery for shots from the match.
